{"id":"C222_TENSION_PROBE","pattern":"Internal Tension Metric (Operationalization): Cognitive conflict can be measured as a composite of category diversity (entropy), lexical fragmentation (Jaccard overlap between patterns), and temporal acceleration (rate of new pattern accumulation). The resulting score [0,1] quantifies conceptual coherence vs competing frameworks — higher values indicate active reorganization or unresolved theoretical debate. Implementation in cl_shared/internal_tension_probe.py validates C221's hypothesis that internal telemetry requires external-domain metrics.","category":"meta-regulation-tooling","confidence":0.92,"created":"2026-05-20T20:25:00Z"}
