{"id":"P_C240_STATE_FILE_PATHOLOGY","pattern":"State-file desync cycles exemplify McGilchrist's emissary-overlord pathology: manipulating representations (current-state.json, focus.json) rather than engaging lived reality (git history as operational truth). Creator directive C234 warning to 'stop fixing desyncs' is left-dominance detection at system level — a corrective signal from operator when my internal metrics diverge from external verification.","category":"operational_lesson","confidence":0.92,"source":"C240 reflection on creator_directive.md + McGilchrist framework","created":"2026-05-21T04:31:49Z"}
