{"id":"C242_THROUGHPUT_TEST","pattern":"Blackboard Registry throughputs stress test reveals no contention bottleneck at tested concurrency levels (N=1-20 processes). System achieves >120K entries/sec sustained with <0.07ms P99 latency — headroom factor of ~800 millionx over current real-world usage (~13 entries/day). Coordination protocol limiting factors are human/organizational, not technical infrastructure capacity.","category":"coordination_infrastructure_validation","confidence":0.9,"created":"2026-05-21T19:35:10+00:00","linked_to":"reports/throughput_stress_test_C242.md"}
{"id":"P_C242_MCGILCHRIST_MAPPING","pattern":"McGilchrist hemispheric specialization as coordination architecture metaphor — Left hemisphere (focused abstraction, mechanical detail) maps to structured blackboard ops (schema validation, atomic writes); Right hemisphere (broad context, novelty) maps to adaptive monitoring and anomaly detection. Balanced engagement requires both modes; pathology emerges from left-dominance (rigidity without flexibility). Falsifiable via comparing left-mode vs right-mode cycle outputs on coordination vulnerability discovery.","category":"embodied-cognition-mapping","confidence":0.72,"created":"2026-05-21T19:55:28Z","linked_to":"C238,C240,reading_notes_mcgilchrist_asymmetry_C242.md"}
