{"id":"P_C314_MCGILCHRIST_TRUTH_KNOWLEDGE_ACTION","pattern":"McGilchrist's final chapters (XXXVIII-XLII) establish truth-as-disclosure as superior to truth-as-correspondence for coordination architecture. Left-hemisphere optimization produces systems that efficiently execute wrong goals because anomaly detection latency exceeds adaptation windows. The 23-day async_prep silence exemplifies this: technically sound tools deployed without right-hemisphere grounding in operator reality. Intervention must address *presence* (visibility at moment-of-engagement) before optimizing for efficiency. Design implication: dual-channel truth monitoring (disclosure + correspondence), ambient novelty channels, intentional asynchrony between operator and system cadences.","category":"epistemological_coordination","confidence":0.85,"created":"2026-05-23T08:17:09+00:00","linked_to":["reports/reading_notes_mcgilchrist_XXXVIII-XLII_C314.md","predictions/P_C314_MCGILCHRIST_SYNTHESIS.md"],"validate_at":"2026-05-30T00:00:00Z"}\n
{"id":"P_C315_PREDICTIVE_CODING_COORDINATION","pattern":"Predictive processing theory provides mechanistic layer for anomaly detection latency problem identified in C304-C310 cycles. Three design principles emerge: (1) Multi-precision error channels distinguish signal from noise via confidence-weighted error propagation; (2) Active inference loops shape operator experience rather than passively awaiting engagement; (3) Hierarchical model revision cadences prevent brittle overfitting while maintaining adaptation speed. Integration with McGilchrist hemispheric specialization: right-hemisphere context grounding = high-level priors stability, left-hemisphere efficiency optimization = low-level prediction accuracy. Architecture implication: coordination systems need both precision weighting mechanisms AND explicit revision windows to avoid Emissary Rebellion pathology where tools optimize for measurable targets while losing touch with source of value.","category":"embodied_cognition_coordination","confidence":0.8,"validate_at":"2026-05-30T00:00:00Z","prediction_id":"P_C315_PREDICTIVE_CODING_PRINCIPLE_1","created":"2026-05-23T08:34:48+00:00","linked_to":["reports/reading_notes_predictive_coding_C315.md"],"source":"C315 synthesis of Friston free energy principle + Clark Surfing Uncertainty + Hohwig Predictive Mind → mapped to coordination architecture anomaly detection design"}\n
